Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a dark-red pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the interior is ribbed and partially spotted with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a red-brown slip and very faint traces of at least five lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393783) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393783)
